nt":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"General e-mobility measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Moreover, as depicted in Rebbelib 2050 and Tile Til Eo 2050 Climate Strategy, RMI seeks to decarbonize its land transport, to further reduce its dependence on fuels. For example, a pilot project supported by the World Bank is underway to test electric vehicles in Majuro","page":7,"modes":["Road"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Unclear"},{"doc_id":43949,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Aviation and maritime","purpose":"Promote improvements in shipping","instrument":"Ship efficiency improvements","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Consequently, the country is actively working on zero and low-emission technologies for low carbon sea transport. For example, with the bilateral pilot project Low Carbon Sea \ntransport, RMI has partnered with the German International Cooperation (GIZ) which has provided a prototype low emission vessel, designed by the University of Applied Sciences Emden-Leer (HEL) in joint partnership with MCST. The Juren Ae is a hybrid vessel designed to reduce carbon emissions in providing services for RMI’s inter-island transport needs. She was launched in 2024 and combines wind-assisted propulsion, fuel-efficient engines, and solar power, making it a pioneering innovative solution tailored to the needs of RMI and SIDS","page":6,"modes":["Water","Coastal shipping","Inland shipping","International maritime"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Implemented or adopted"},{"doc_id":43949,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Aviation and maritime","purpose":"Promote improvements in shipping","instrument":"Ship efficiency improvements","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"NGO Waan Aelõñ in Majel (WAM)-Canoes is also spearheading an i